Problem Definitions for AJAX
1. Make a database table of ‘country’.
a. Add 4 countries.
2. Make a database table of ‘state’. 
a.  State must reference to their relevant row in country table.
b. Add 3 states per countries.
3. Make a database table of ‘city. 
a.  City must reference to their relevant row in state and country table.
b. Add 3 cities per state.
4. List all countries in dropdown.
5. List all states of selected country using simple Ajax, when a country is changed.
a. Selection box of states should get blank when no country is selected.
6. List all cities of selected state using jQuery and Ajax, when a state is changed.
a. Selection box of cities should get blank when no country and/or state is selected.
